result.name: Eight Treasures

reviews.text: Simple, classic Taiwanese food that won't break the bank. Mind you, this is not luxury dining, but if you have a craving for high-quality noodles and fresh ingredients in Taiwanese style this is a great one that is affordable enough that you can keep coming back.

My first visit. This place offers nothing but beef brisket on noodles or rice. The stock broth on the noodles is unique with strong flavor of Chinese herbal medicine. Brisket is full of flavor and tenderness. 4 points for the food. Seatings and a lack of English menu took one point away. Go with a local who can help you with the ordering. Spent $100 per head.
Local HK style beef noodle soup. You can choose the preferred parts of the beef and different kind of noodles. Super tendon and the broth tastes herbal. Great for winter. Would definitely return.
The Best beef brisket noodle experience in HK! Pick your noodles and go for the "hang nam" brisket. It is so fatty and tender. It's a once a week thing for me.
Pretty average noodle shop. They do serve a wide array of choices, but I had the first one and it was comparable to many other noodle shops. Okay place, nothing special.
